<TITLE> Bangladesh snatch SAG soccer gold </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 8 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh trounced Afghanistan 4-0 to snatch the SAG soccer gold on Monday, after 11 years. The host country dominated the first half taking a lead of 2-0. Atiqur Rahman Mishu scored the first goal in the 18th minute. Enamul Haque established Bangladesh's dominance on the field in the 32nd minute doubling the margin. Abdul Baten Kollol found the net in the 69th minute leaving the Afghan players into total disarray, with Touhidul Islam Sabuj smashing home the fourth goal with minutes to go before the end of play. Bangladesh won its last South Asian Games soccer gold in 1999.
